column6: Aphasia can cause difficulties producing speech in a number of ways through the inability to produce words, or the inability to produce correct words. It seems like experiencing aphasia would be a deeply isolating and frustrating experience. My college advisor was experiencing early onset dementia with aphasia as a symptom, and even when we as students were happy to be patient and helpful, it was really emotionally damaging to him. When talking to him it was clear that he was a very smart man who felt like he was trapped.
